## Functions

### forceAttributes() {#a447453362ec26907f4116a81d6ac91f1}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>static void forceAttributes (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/function">Function</a> &amp; F)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
If F has any forced attributes given on the command line, add them.

If F has any forced remove attributes given on the command line, remove them. When both force and force-remove are given to a function, the latter takes precedence.

Definition at line <a href="#l00051">51</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/transforms/lib/transforms/ipo/forcefunctionattrs-cpp">ForceFunctionAttrs.cpp</a>.
